    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Bash your <strong>lemongrass</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong>, then remove the <strong>tough outer layers</strong> of your lemongrass<strong> </strong>and set aside for later </p><p>Chop the <strong>softer inner core[s]</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-chilli-chicken-tray-bake-with-lemongrass-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[390ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [600ml]<strong> </strong></span><strong>boiled water</strong> and the <strong>outer lemongrass layers </strong></p><p>Cover tightly with <strong>tin foil</strong> and put the dish in the oven for 30 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked \u2013 this is your <strong>baked lemongrass rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-chilli-chicken-tray-bake-with-lemongrass-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into batons (no need to peel!)</p><p>Peel and chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Trim your <strong>green beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-chilli-chicken-tray-bake-with-lemongrass-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> pho broth paste </strong>to a bowl<strong> </strong>with your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>chopped lemongrass</strong>, <strong>honey</strong>,<strong> soy sauce </strong>and<strong> chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>honey chilli sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-chilli-chicken-tray-bake-with-lemongrass-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chicken</strong>,<strong> onion wedges</strong> and <strong>carrot batons</strong> to a <strong>tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!)</p><p>Pour the <strong>honey chilli sauce </strong>over the top</p><p>Put the tray[s]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>in the oven and cook for an initial 15-17 min or until the vegetables have softened</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-chilli-chicken-tray-bake-with-lemongrass-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Use this time to clear up, set the table, have a cup of tea or simply chill!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-chilli-chicken-tray-bake-with-lemongrass-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After an initial 15-17 min, remove the tray[s] from the oven</p><p>Add the <strong>trimmed green beans </strong>to the top of the tray[s]</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven for a final 10-12 min or until everything is tender and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>honey chilli chicken traybake</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/honey-chilli-chicken-tray-bake-with-lemongrass-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Discard the <strong>lemongrass</strong> from the rice</p><p>Serve the<strong> honey chilli chicken traybake</strong> with the<strong> baked lemongrass rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle any <strong>remaining cooking juices</strong> from the baking tray[s] all over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
